---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="About — MacroChat AI">
  <section class="band">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:760px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">About us</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.2rem,6vw,4rem); margin:1.2rem 0 1.5rem;">Honest numbers,<br /><span style="background:var(--amber); padding:0 0.4rem;">zero guesswork.</span></h1>

      <div class="block" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Why MacroChat exists</h3>
        <p>Most calorie apps make you search dropdowns and weigh everything. Most AI
        trackers just let the model invent numbers. MacroChat does neither: you talk
        to it like a person — "200g grilled chicken, 2 rotis" or a photo — and every
        calorie it reports comes from a real nutrition database, never from the AI's
        imagination.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="block" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.6rem;">How we keep it honest</h3>
        <p>The AI's only job is identifying food and reasoning about portions. Macros
        come from the Indian Nutrient Databank (INDB) and USDA FoodData Central. Daily
        totals are computed in the backend, not by a language model. When we estimate
        a portion from a photo, we say so — and ask you to confirm before it counts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="block">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Built for Indian plates too</h3>
        <p>Roti, dal, sabzi, biryani — 1,000+ Indian recipes and ingredients from INDB,
        with USDA covering everything else. One tracker for both halves of your diet.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
